# Single source of truth for tool versions. asdf/mise compatible.
#
# Why: Phase 0 of the rendered-manifests migration pins all CI/render
# tools to deterministic versions to prevent helm-template/kustomize-build
# output drift between local developer machines and CI.
#
# CI workflows reference these versions via env vars; the `verify-tools`
# Makefile target reads this file and confirms installed binaries match.
# A drift-check step in gitops-validate.yml fails if the workflow env
# vars and this file disagree.
#
# Update workflow: bump version here, then update matching env vars in
# .github/workflows/{gitops-validate,oci-publish}.yml, then run
# `make verify-tools` locally to confirm.
helm 3.20.2
kustomize 5.3.0
oras 1.2.0
cosign 2.4.1
conftest 0.53.0
kyverno-cli 1.17.1
kubeconform 0.6.7
